League 1
Rennes: Camavinga, naturalized French!
As announced a few hours ago, the young Rennes midfielder Eduardo Camavinga, was naturalized French as he announced his way on the networks
04 Nov 2019, 20:35 by Charlie Creteur



16-year-old Eduardo Camavinga, staggering with Stade Rennais from Steve Mandanda to Memphis Depay, to the young Eduardo Camavinga, several individuals emerged from the lot this weekend, on the occasion of the second day of Ligue 1. Icon Sport Overview

Mandanda, Camavinga, Memphis, ... the typical team of the weekend in Ligue 1




It was expected, Eduardo Camavinga now has French nationality. A few hours earlier, the daily L'Equipe, evoked the outcome of the naturalization file of the young community of Rennes born in Cabinda in Angola. This seems now done as the player announced on Twitter with tricolor flags. A beautiful birthday present before celebrating its 17th birthday on November 10th!
